<bug>
	<id>108729</id>
	<title>CVS Checkout consistently crashes</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">This problem is only reproducible on a particular computer; I assume it is a</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.2">configuration issue on this computer but I cannot see what is going wrong or how</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.3">to fix it.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.4">After downloading 3.1 and installing CDT (have not tried this without</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.5">CDT), I attempt to check out a project.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.6">It is a large-ish project, and so the</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.7">checkout takes approximately ten minutes on a working machine.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.8">On this machine,</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.9">however, it fails during checkout.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.10">The point at which it fails is not consistent.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.11">There have been other things that do not seem to work on this machine, and I am</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.12">including them here in case they ring any bells for you.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.13">1 It could not download the Eclipse SDK zip file itself - it failed several</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.14">times after getting around 70-80%.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.15">Eventually the zip was downloaded from</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.16">another machine and copied to it, after which things worked fine.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.17">2 On installing Eclipse, some icons appeared as black, and some text failed to</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.18">render.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.19">After consulting Bugzilla, we determined that this was a problem with</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.20">MacAfee.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.21">Downloading the recommended patch did not fix the problem; however,</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.22">disabling buffer-overflow protection did fix it.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">Note that a command-line checkout of this project works fine.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">I will add crash logs momentarily.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.3">There are five of them, and I don't know how
much is the unique/important, so I will include them all.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
